{
  "text": "The second contribution of our work is the novel in-vivo tractography validation framework that we used. In contrast to previous techniques, we propose to use the already known anatomical information based on the topographically organized connections in the brain. To achieve this, we developed two independent techniques. Our first approach is based on the visual pathway that is retinotopically organized [CITATION_1] . The second approach is based on a mathematical formulation of the neuroscientific understanding of topographic regularity, which implies the preservation of the spatial relationships between the end points of axonal projections. In our literature review, we were not able to find any other example of a validation approach for topographic regularity of tractograms.",
